================================================================================
Prior art and attribution
================================================================================

Asymmetry is a from-scratch Python toolkit for muon-spin spectroscopy (μSR) data
analysis. Its analysis methods, fit models, data conventions, and file-format
support were learned by studying established μSR programs and the μSR literature,
and were then INDEPENDENTLY REIMPLEMENTED in Python. No source code from any of
the programs below was copied, transcribed, or mechanically translated into this
repository. Shared elements are unprotectable facts: mathematical formulae,
physical constants, published algorithms, and documented file-format layouts.
Where the implementation follows one of these programs, the relevant source file
or docstring cites it; the study notes live under docs/porting/.

We gratefully acknowledge the following projects and their authors:

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
WiMDA
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A muon-spin-spectroscopy data-analysis program by Francis L. Pratt (ISIS Muon
Group). WiMDA is freely-available freeware; its source code is not published
under an open-source licence and remains the author's. Asymmetry reimplements a
number of WiMDA's fit functions, asymmetry/grouping conventions, frequency- and
count-domain methods, and maximum-entropy reconstruction from the documented
mathematics and observable behaviour only.

  F. L. Pratt, "WiMDA: a muon data analysis program for the Windows PC",
  Physica B 289-290, 710-714 (2000).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
musrfit
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
An open-source μSR fitting framework. Licensed under the GNU General Public
License. Asymmetry's PSI-BIN/MDU and MusrRoot readers were written from the
documented binary/file-format layouts (a file format is a fact, not copyrightable
expression); no musrfit source was incorporated.

  A. Suter and B. M. Wojek, "Musrfit: A Free Platform-Independent Framework for
  muSR Data Analysis", Physics Procedia 30, 69-73 (2012).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Mantid
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
An open-source data-reduction and analysis framework. Licensed under the GNU
General Public License v3. Asymmetry's NeXus muon loading, asymmetry/alpha
conventions, deadtime handling, and ALC field-scan workflow were studied from
Mantid's documented behaviour and reimplemented independently.

  O. Arnold et al., "Mantid - Data analysis and visualization package for
  neutron scattering and muSR experiments", Nucl. Instrum. Methods A 764,
  156-166 (2014).

